WorkItem.Description:
I have generated an excel file with multiple sheets (used as references;) and set the values for a column with a Vlookup formula.
I am setting this values in a Z sheet.
Here is the formula.
$formula = VLOOKUP($X.C3,$'Y'.A2:B25,2,0)

The excel sheet has the expected value. But when i try to read this values in php i get a value '#N/A'

I Also tried the IFERROR condition like this:
$formula =IFERROR(VLOOKUP($X.C3,$'Y'.A2:B25,2,0),"Something is wrong?")

The cells have the right values but when i read them in php i get the specified error("Something is wrong?").

I tried reading the cell values with getCalculatedValue() but doesn't work. Kindly help.
